    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2797" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἴρω</span></b>  (1) (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝερ</span>, cf. verbum), assumed pres. for fut.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐρέω, -έει, -έουσι</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐρέων, ἐρέουσα</span>, pass. perf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἴρηται</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἰρημένος</span>, plup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἴρητο</span>,
          fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἰρήσεται</span>, aor. part. dat. sing.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥηθέντι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">say, speak,
            declare;</span> strictly with regard merely to the words said;
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">announce, herald</span>, (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἠώς</span>) <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ζηνὶ φόως ἐρέουσα</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 2.49</span></i>; (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἑωσφόρος</span>) <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φόως ἐρέων ἐπὶ
            γαῖαν</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
          23.226</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
